race.comment: SHE IS ALL MAGIC (4) hasn't made an impression lately despite market confidence. Last start could only manage fifth over 1000m at Bairnsdale. Likely improver who should be in the finish this time. STATESMANSHIP (1) turned in another moderate effort last start when 5 lengths from the winner in seventh over 1457m at Kilmore. Has his share of talent and is a top-three prospect. GAME THEORY (9) was below his best last time when seventh over 1600m at Tatura, beaten 7 lengths. Looks well placed so expect a big run this time. MAHJING (8) missed the placings two runs back then was always well out of his ground last start when 8 lengths away in eighth over 1200m at Wodonga. Is unbeaten in two starts at this course and distance. Best figures measure up nicely. Sure to run well.
